# Copy to .env.local. Devnet only.

# Privy App ID (public, client-side). Create at dashboard.privy.io:
#   - enable Google login
#   - enable embedded Solana wallets (create on login)
#   - Solana devnet
# Until this is set, the end-user login screens show a "configure Privy" notice.
NEXT_PUBLIC_PRIVY_APP_ID=

# SERVER-ONLY. getProgramAccounts-capable devnet RPC (Helius). If unset, falls
# back to the public devnet RPC — fine for this app (no getProgramAccounts
# calls on the hot path). The browser talks to /api/rpc, which proxies to this
# — never exposed to the browser directly.
# HELIUS_RPC_URL=

# SERVER-ONLY. Same Supabase project the Railway poller (oracle-service/src/
# poller.cjs) writes to — this app only ever READS from it (schedule + match
# results). Use the SERVICE ROLE key (not anon); this table has no public RLS
# policy, so anon would get zero rows back.
SUPABASE_URL=
SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=

# NOTE: TXLINE_API_TOKEN is intentionally NOT needed here anymore — the app no
# longer calls TxLINE directly (see oracle-service/src/poller.cjs). The token
# only needs to be set in oracle-service/.env.
